Yes, right now this page is **hardcoded in French**, except the `<title>` already uses:

```html
<title th:text="#{pageTitle}">Choix point de vente</title>
```

So the browser title can translate, but the visible screen content cannot because these are plain French strings:

```html
<h1>Connexion à<br>votre espace partenaire</h1>
<h2>Votre point de vente</h2>
<p>Vous devez choisir le point de vente dans lequel vous vous trouvez actuellement.</p>
<button>Confirmer ...</button>
```

Update them to message keys like this:

```html
<h1 th:utext="#{salesPoints.heading}">
    Connexion à<br>votre espace partenaire
</h1>

<h2 th:text="#{salesPoints.title}">
    Votre point de vente
</h2>

<p th:text="#{salesPoints.description}">
    Vous devez choisir le point de vente dans lequel vous vous trouvez actuellement.
</p>

<button class="confirm-btn" type="submit">
    <span th:text="#{salesPoints.confirm}">Confirmer</span>
    <img th:src="@{/images/icons/arrow-forward.svg}"
         th:alt="#{salesPoints.confirm}"
         class="btn-icon">
</button>
```

For the language buttons, also make them dynamic:

```html
<div class="language-selector">
    <a th:href="@{/sales-points(appId=${appId}, lang='fr')}"
       th:classappend="${#locale.language == 'fr'} ? ' active' : ''"
       class="language-btn">FR</a>

    <a th:href="@{/sales-points(appId=${appId}, lang='nl')}"
       th:classappend="${#locale.language == 'nl'} ? ' active' : ''"
       class="language-btn">NL</a>
</div>
```

Then add/update your message files.

`messages_fr.properties`:

```properties
pageTitle=Choix point de vente

salesPoints.heading=Connexion à<br>votre espace partenaire
salesPoints.title=Votre point de vente
salesPoints.description=Vous devez choisir le point de vente dans lequel vous vous trouvez actuellement.
salesPoints.confirm=Confirmer
```

`messages_nl.properties`:

```properties
pageTitle=Keuze verkooppunt

salesPoints.heading=Verbinding met<br>uw partneromgeving
salesPoints.title=Uw verkooppunt
salesPoints.description=U moet het verkooppunt kiezen waar u zich momenteel bevindt.
salesPoints.confirm=Bevestigen
```

Because `salesPoints.heading` contains `<br>`, use `th:utext` only for that one. For the rest, use `th:text`.

For your custom title font, put the font file here:

```text
src/main/resources/static/fonts/
```

Example:

```text
src/main/resources/static/fonts/title-font.woff2
```

Then add this at the top of `sales-points.css`:

```css
@font-face {
  font-family: 'SalesPointTitle';
  src: url('/fonts/title-font.woff2') format('woff2');
  font-weight: 400;
  font-style: normal;
  font-display: swap;
}
```

And apply it to your main title:

```css
.left-content h1 {
  font-family: 'SalesPointTitle', Arial, sans-serif;
}
```

One important thing: your `<button type="button">FR</button>` and `<button type="button">NL</button>` currently do nothing unless JavaScript is attached. Using `<a th:href=...>` is easier and works immediately with Spring locale switching.
